== Board of governors ==
Each year the membership of the National Academy of Television Arts & Sciences Ohio Valley Chapter elects new professionals on a two year rotating Board of Governors to represent the Ohio Valley community. While best known for The EMMYÂ® Awards and Silver Circle, which recognize outstanding achievements in our industry, NATAS Ohio Valley represents an array of other exciting events available to their membership.
The Board of Governors is a working board which work together collaboratively to ensures the best interests of the membership.<ref name="urlNATAS Ohio Valley Chapter">{{cite web |url=http://www.ohiovalleyemmy.org/about/bog_and_staff.stm |title=NATAS Ohio Valley Chapter |author=[[NATAS]] |authorlink= |coauthors= |date= |work= |publisher= |pages= |language= |archiveurl= |archivedate= |quote= |accessdate=2010-07-18}}Board of Governors</ref>
